Fun story for my daughter's first time voting. My kids go to the same college (University of Puget Sound, in Tacoma WA), and they had last long weekend (Saturday - Tuesday) off as an after-midterm fall break. My son came home to visit (SF Bay Area), but my daughter went to visit her friend in LA, and had a direct flight back to school on Monday. My husband, son and I filled out our ballots together over the weekend, and were going to put them in the dropbox on Monday. My son was going to bring his sister's ballot back to school so she could fill it out and mail it. Well, my daughter's flight was cancelled, and she was put on a new flight late on Monday night, flying through SF. She decided to extend her layover so she could fly back with my son on Tuesday, so we got to have her home overnight.
